[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     86[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The standard Platt scaling formulation transforms a raw model score (which may be a logit or uncalibrated probability) through `1 / (1 + exp(-(a*x + b)))`. When the input `x` is already a probability in [0, 1] (as it is here from `predict_proba`), the transform compresses the output range significantly. With `a = -1.2` and `b = 0.3`:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     87[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Input 0.5 maps to output 0.426
